cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about single image super resolution (SISR), which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes an attention-based approach, which involves identifying high frequency areas and compensating for them. This approach involves using neural networks, which suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves image processing, which could also place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
